# tea-db ingest schedule (V1.1 ops template).
#
# Hourly Shopify scrapes, staggered per-vendor over a 60-minute window so
# no single Shopify CDN sees the project's traffic as bursty. The 15-minute
# stagger isn't load-bearing — anything that breaks up bursts is fine; the
# point is to avoid running `tea-scrape ingest shopify --all` in one go.
#
# Rationale: specs/tea_scrapers_v1_spec.md §12 (Shopify storefront bot
# mitigation) + tech-lead audit 2026-05-16. Running --all from a single IP
# in a short window triggered Cloudflare 403s on 3 of 4 vendors during
# the step-4 smoke test.
#
# This file is a template, NOT a wired-up cron. ROADMAP step 10 lands the
# actual cron integration (shell wrappers, env sourcing, log rotation).
#
# Setup before installing:
#   1. Replace /path/to/tea-db with the absolute path to your checkout.
#   2. Ensure ~/.venvs/tea-scrapers/bin is the venv path the project uses
#      (or substitute your venv path).
#   3. Source the project's .env so USER_AGENT / DATABASE_URL / etc. are set:
#        env $(cat /path/to/tea-db/tea-scrapers/.env | xargs) tea-scrape ...
#      or use a wrapper shell script (preferred for step 10).
#   4. Create /var/log/tea-db/ with appropriate permissions, or redirect
#      logs elsewhere.
#
# Install with: crontab tea-scrapers/scripts/crontab.example

# Minute  5 — yunnan_sourcing_us
5  * * * * cd /path/to/tea-db/tea-scrapers && ~/.venvs/tea-scrapers/bin/tea-scrape ingest shopify --vendor yunnan_sourcing_us >> /var/log/tea-db/yunnan_sourcing_us.log 2>&1

# Minute 20 — yunnan_sourcing_com
20 * * * * cd /path/to/tea-db/tea-scrapers && ~/.venvs/tea-scrapers/bin/tea-scrape ingest shopify --vendor yunnan_sourcing_com >> /var/log/tea-db/yunnan_sourcing_com.log 2>&1

# Minute 35 — white2tea
35 * * * * cd /path/to/tea-db/tea-scrapers && ~/.venvs/tea-scrapers/bin/tea-scrape ingest shopify --vendor white2tea >> /var/log/tea-db/white2tea.log 2>&1

# Minute 50 — crimson_lotus
50 * * * * cd /path/to/tea-db/tea-scrapers && ~/.venvs/tea-scrapers/bin/tea-scrape ingest shopify --vendor crimson_lotus >> /var/log/tea-db/crimson_lotus.log 2>&1

# Daily bronze + silver pipeline at 02:00 UTC, after all 4 vendors have
# landed at least one hour of scrapes. `date -u -v-1d` is the macOS form;
# Linux operators want `date -u --date='1 day ago'` instead.
0 2 * * * cd /path/to/tea-db/tea-scrapers && ~/.venvs/tea-scrapers/bin/tea-scrape load --since $(date -u -v-1d +\%Y-\%m-\%d) >> /var/log/tea-db/load.log 2>&1
5 2 * * * cd /path/to/tea-db/tea-scrapers && ~/.venvs/tea-scrapers/bin/tea-scrape normalize --since $(date -u -v-1d +\%Y-\%m-\%d) >> /var/log/tea-db/normalize.log 2>&1
